.SH NAME
HTMLAnchorElement.hreflang \- HTMLAnchorElement: hreflang property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hreflang\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLAnchorElement\f[R] interface is a string that is the language
of the linked resource.
.PP
It reflects the \f[CR]hreflang\f[R] attribute of the \f[CR]<a>\f[R]
element and is the empty string (\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]) if there is no
\f[CR]hreflang\f[R] element.
.PP
Web browsers and search engines may use this information to understand
the language of the linked content better, but they are not required to
follow it.
The value provided for the \f[CR]hreflang\f[R] attribute adheres to the
format defined in RFC 5646: Tags for Identifying Languages (also known
as BCP 47).
If not, it is ignored.
.PP
Web browsers do not rely solely on the \f[CR]hreflang\f[R] attribute
after fetching the linked resource.
Instead, they use language information directly associated with the
resource (e.g., through HTTP headers) to determine its language.
.SH VALUE
A string that contains a language tag, or the empty string
(\f[CR]\(dq\(dq\f[R]) if there is no \f[CR]hreflang\f[R] element.
